#3 main branches here:

stable: it's stable, well understood, limited risks but fewer features
main: the workhorse, supported but features are merged in from experimental
experimental: is experimental, things may break but has the most and newest features


#Instructions for geometry display

mkdir build
cd build
cmake ..
make
./make_leadplate_db
gmex geometry.db

changes in calo.cfg should be reflected in the geometry after running


#Instruction for simulation run

mkdir build
cd build
cmake ..
make
./run_g4

you can change parameters in .cfg files
